I don't want to hurt you anymore.

12:32.461 --> 12:33.670
I really don't want to lose you.

12:33.670 --> 12:36.798
‐ How do I know that
any of that shit is true?

12:36.798 --> 12:38.383
‐ I'll do anything to prove it.
‐ Anything?

12:38.383 --> 12:41.136
‐ Yes, please.
‐ I want this to be a real relationship.

12:41.136 --> 12:43.013
‐ This is a real relationship.
‐ No, it's not.

12:43.680 --> 12:46.391
I'm too old to be confused
like this, okay?

12:46.391 --> 12:49.102
It's nothing to do with sex, or monogamy.

12:49.394 --> 12:52.231
You have never committed to me.
Ever.

12:52.231 --> 12:54.441
You could just disappear at any minute

12:54.441 --> 12:56.610
because I don't know what the fuck we are.

12:57.110 --> 12:59.863
<i>I don't know if it was</i>
<i>a sick Jedi mind trick</i>

13:00.197 --> 13:01.782
<i>or if he really wanted to commit.</i>

13:01.782 --> 13:04.868
‐ Let me be clear then,
nothing would make me happier

13:04.868 --> 13:06.411
than being your boyfriend.

13:06.411 --> 13:08.830
SIMON:
<i>It doesn't matter now, but then,</i>

13:10.082 --> 13:11.500
<i>[sighs] I bought it all the way.</i>

13:12.417 --> 13:15.254
<i>The next few weeks, we spent</i>
<i>every free moment together.</i>

13:15.254 --> 13:17.172
<i>Ben was finally my boyfriend.</i>

13:17.172 --> 13:19.591
<i>My first real boyfriend.</i>

13:19.591 --> 13:21.301
‐ Uh... I'll have an old fashioned

13:21.301 --> 13:23.929
and a whiskey neat

13:23.929 --> 13:25.722
