to listen to <i>Disco Duck.</i>

14:32.664 --> 14:34.583
But you can't dismiss the whole genre.

14:34.583 --> 14:36.376
It made a huge impact.

14:37.127 --> 14:39.713
Like, almost every early hip‐hop song
sampled a disco track.

14:40.339 --> 14:41.507
Plus, Sylvester was an icon.

14:42.633 --> 14:44.009
He was androgynous, you know,

14:44.009 --> 14:46.303
and he would wear
women's clothes on stage.

14:47.179 --> 14:50.933
Not in, like, a '60s rock star,
Marc Bolan kind of way

14:50.933 --> 14:53.560
but in a way that felt... complete

14:53.977 --> 14:55.854
and sincere and organic.

14:57.022 --> 14:58.148
It was just a part of him.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.901
His first group was called
"The Cockettes."

15:00.901 --> 15:04.029
That is next level not giving a shit.

15:04.821 --> 15:06.323
Listen to that crazy falsetto.

15:07.157 --> 15:08.825
It's, the guy is a legend,

15:08.825 --> 15:10.410
and you have to respect the legends.

15:12.246 --> 15:13.288
‐ Wow.

15:14.289 --> 15:15.290
‐ What?

15:16.583 --> 15:19.086
‐ It's just... when you get
this passionate.

15:20.796 --> 15:22.464
It's perfect. You're perfect.

15:22.464 --> 15:25.884
♪

15:29.763 --> 15:31.098
SIMON:
<i>It felt like the right moment.</i>

15:31.098 --> 15:33.475
♪

15:33.475 --> 15:34.434
I love you.

15:35.227 --> 15:38.397
[cell phone buzzing]

15:41.525 --> 15:42.693
‐ It's work. I gotta‐‐

15:43.610 --> 15:45.696
♪

15:50.325 --> 15:51.785
<i>‐ It was not the right moment.</i>

15:55.330 --> 15:59.418
